{
  "texts": [
    "In that case, they may become less adept at critically evaluating their work and identifying improvement areas.",
    "Second, there might be the issue of unquestioning acceptance of feedback.",
    "Automation bias may lead students to accept feedback provided by AI-based tools without critically evaluating its accuracy or considering alternative perspectives.",
    "This uncritical acceptance could hinder students' development of essential self-assessment and self-regulation skills.",
    "Stakeholders of educational assessments should ensure that automation serves as a valuable tool for enhancing, rather than detracting from, the assessment experience for all students.Ethical discussions around automation bias extend to considerations of education and training (Rahm, 2023)."
  ]
}